President Obama and his wife, Michelle, expressed their condolences to the families of the six US Airmen and five contractors who died in a military plane crash in Afghanistan. They also expressed sympathy for the Afghan civilians who lost their lives in the incident. The President highlighted the sacrifices made by American and Afghan servicemen and women in the pursuit of freedom and security. He assured that their selfless service will not be forgotten and offered thoughts and prayers to the victims' families and loved ones.